Package solver.reachablepoints.graph

Class GraphCalculation

  • java.lang.Object
    • solver.reachablepoints.graph.GraphCalculation
  • public class GraphCalculation
extends Object
    Calculation object for calculating success and cut off ratings based on some initial players until a IDeadline is reached. Calculations are graph-based and queued up based on their local solution improvement and a small random value.

        Parameters:
        graph - the Graph board to find the edges
        probabilities - FloatMatrix with probabilities
        minSteps - FloatMatrix with minimum steps
        initialEdges - all possible Edges the player can do for the current round
        deadline - IDeadline to limit execution time
        queueSize - the maximum Size of elements for each of the 5 queues
